# HTB - Redeemer (Tier 0)
**Difficulty:** Very Easy
**OS:** Linux

## Tools Used
- nmap
- redis-cli

## Steps
1. Connected Kali VM to HTB network via OpenVPN
2. Default nmap missed Redis — ran `nmap -sV -p 6379 <IP>`
3. Found port 6379 (Redis) open
4. Connected using `redis-cli -h <IP>`
5. Ran `info` to get server information
6. Ran `keys *` to list all keys
7. Retrieved flag using `get flag`

## What I Learned
- Default nmap only scans top 1000 ports — always scan specific ports if service is suspected
- Redis without authentication exposes all stored data
- Misconfigured databases are a serious real-world risk
